The 36-year-old suspect was arrested at his house in Seshego outside Polokwane where over 1,700 boxes were seized. JOHANNESBURG Limpopo police have arrested a man found in possession of counterfeit cigarettes worth an estimated value of R258,000.The 36-year-old suspect was arrested at his house in Seshego outside Polokwane where over 1,700 boxes were seized.Police a Nissan bakkie believed to be used in transporting the cigarettes was also confiscated.The police's Moatshe Ngoepe said, The suspect will appear in the Seshego Magistrates Court soon. Investigations are continuing. 